	<section class="grid align-center page-section">
		<div class="col-2_sm-2_xs-12">
			<h5>PROCESS</h5>
		</div>
		<div class="col-7_sm-9">
			<div class="title-headerline"> </div>
		</div>

		<div class="grid align-center">
			<div class="col-7_lg-8_sm-10_xs-12">
				<div class="page-paragraph_block">
					<p>Based on the above research, I identified the biggest issues with the current Stats Lab experience, and gathered a few solutions based on other statistics sites I viewed. The current experience does a fantastic job of handling the sheer quantity of data and supporting the statistics used in the OWL broadcast, but the core platform is not very user-friendly, and the different views are confusing and overwhelming to first-time viewers. It can be difficult to navigate, with unclear labels and a lack of descriptive language. Along with long load times from the Tableau embed, awkward controls, many large tables of data with no clear visual hierarchies, and confusing filter options, the overall experience creates a steep learning curve.</p>
					<p>Identifying these problems helped me establish three core concepts to center this project around - <b>time, context and ease-of-use</b>. Designing for time is necessary to capture the ever-changing landscape of the game and league, playstyle and strategies change constantly as the game is updated, and it’s important to be able to track that via stats, whether through team oriented metrics or individual performance numbers over time. This type of comparison, when combined with the third idea of adding context, the most important of the three, helps provide the viewer a deeper understanding of the statistic they are viewing. In such a fluid, complex, and team oriented game, it is <b>essential that viewers understand the background and circumstances behind a data point</b>, whether comparing individual players, viewing trends over a certain period or time, or trying to identify a certain playstyle. Finally, an overall <b>emphasis on ease-of-use, through clear navigation, filtering options, and organizational details</b>, allows the user to find the data they are looking for and avoid frustration.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>


